.TH "dc_validate_global_state" 9 "dc_validate_global_state" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dc_validate_global_state \- Determine if HW can support a given state Checks HW resource availability and bandwidth requirement.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "enum dc_status" dc_validate_global_state
.BI "(struct dc *dc "  ","
.BI "struct dc_state *new_ctx "  ","
.BI "bool fast_validate "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dc" 12
dc struct for this driver
.IP "new_ctx" 12
state to be validated
.IP "fast_validate" 12
set to true if only yes/no to support matters
.SH "RETURN"
DC_OK if the result can be programmed.  Otherwise, an error code.
